commit.message:
Disable optimsation into C array iteration for iterating string literals inside of generators.

This currently fails to generate valid C code for the generator closure.

See https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7323

Prevent an invalid assignment from a C string array.
Previously, "cdef char[3] name = 'ABC'" tried to cast the C string constant to a C array type and tried to copy that into the stack array.
Disable one more place where carray iteration gets in the way.
Add tests for string iteration in generator expressions.
Make the disabling actually work by setting the scope flag for the GeneratorDefNode (in addition to, but rather should be the GeneratorBodyDefNode).
Disable one more incarnation of bytes iteration in generators.

title: Disable optimisation into C array iteration for iterating string literals inside of generators
